msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/building/development-workflow.rst:27
#: 44bb8bf53cf24d1095e5c1c2f95a2cab
msgid ""
"You can then proceed to easily develop in your own branches, pull in new "
"commits from the dev branches, merge them, and eventually push to your own "
"repo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/building/development-workflow.rst:29
#: aa5f236c2e7241be94ebef19357298b0
msgid ""
"When you are ready to submit your changes to Qubes to be merged, push your "
"changes, then create a signed git tag (using ``git tag -s``). Finally, send "
"a letter to the Qubes listserv describing the changes, and including a link "
"to your repository. If you are using GitHub you can instead create a pull "
"request. Don’t forget to include the public PGP key you use to sign your "
"tags."
msgstr ""

